00:49:29.669 --> 00:49:31.710
And I don't mean to
disparage data-driven design,

00:49:31.710 --> 00:49:33.230
because it is
important to use data

00:49:33.230 --> 00:49:34.580
to inform design decisions.

00:49:34.580 --> 00:49:39.760
But it's also important
to go into this other mode

00:49:39.760 --> 00:49:41.710
of thinking, like the
creative mind is not

00:49:41.710 --> 00:49:42.790
the analytical mind.

00:49:42.790 --> 00:49:45.810
And I hope that people
understand that more

00:49:45.810 --> 00:49:49.430
and appreciate the different
mindsets that you can engage in

00:49:49.430 --> 00:49:53.260
so that you go into the
appropriate frame of mind

00:49:53.260 --> 00:49:56.980
during different parts of
product development and design.

00:49:56.980 --> 00:49:59.960
It was quite a revelation to
me as we developed this design

00:49:59.960 --> 00:50:04.030
sprint methodology when
we deliberately said, OK,

00:50:04.030 --> 00:50:08.240
in this mode we are now entering
divergent thinking mode.

00:50:08.240 --> 00:50:11.800
And whoever's facilitating
these design sprints,

00:50:11.800 --> 00:50:16.370
we trained the facilitators
to embrace every idea

00:50:16.370 --> 00:50:18.540
and to not judge
anything as they get

00:50:18.540 --> 00:50:22.490
generated so that you
can kind of encourage

00:50:22.490 --> 00:50:25.075
a lot of playfulness and a
lot of ideas being generated.

00:50:25.075 --> 00:50:27.450
And then there's a deliberate
break in that design sprint

00:50:27.450 --> 00:50:29.930
phase, where we say,
OK, now is the time

00:50:29.930 --> 00:50:32.320
to prioritize and converge.

00:50:32.320 --> 00:50:35.130
And so it's a way of sneaking
in these different modes

00:50:35.130 --> 00:50:41.500
of thinking without calling on
like anything that might seem

00:50:41.500 --> 00:50:44.570
eerie [INAUDIBLE] or whatever.

00:50:44.570 --> 00:50:46.560
And so as facilitators,
like anyone

00:50:46.560 --> 00:50:49.200
who's facilitating
designs for brainstorms,

00:50:49.200 --> 00:50:56.060
kind of has some ability
to kind of facilitate that

00:50:56.060 --> 00:50:58.680
by saying like, OK,
let's just take a moment

00:50:58.680 --> 00:51:02.350
to be with ourselves as we go
into this phase of the design

00:51:02.350 --> 00:51:03.570
brainstorm, for example.

00:51:03.570 --> 00:51:05.560
AUDIENCE: You're always
