00:51:08.970 --> 00:51:10.500
Speaking to this audience, yeah.

00:51:10.500 --> 00:51:18.519
But that's the culture
that we're in, yeah.

00:51:18.519 --> 00:51:19.954
Yeah?

00:51:19.954 --> 00:51:20.954
AUDIENCE: Two questions.

00:51:20.954 --> 00:51:25.824
What kind of meditation do you
practice regularly, and then

00:51:25.824 --> 00:51:28.989
do you have any advice for
when you kind of get to a point

00:51:28.989 --> 00:51:33.052
where you plateau a little bit
in meditation and mindfulness?

00:51:33.052 --> 00:51:34.260
IRENE AU: That's interesting.

00:51:34.260 --> 00:51:36.330
I never thought of
the word "plateau"

00:51:36.330 --> 00:51:40.100
to describe my own
practice, because I

00:51:40.100 --> 00:51:42.940
don't think of it in terms of
like trying to get anywhere

00:51:42.940 --> 00:51:46.170
or trying to measure it or
evaluate it in some ways.

00:51:46.170 --> 00:51:48.860
It's really about
taking a few moments

00:51:48.860 --> 00:51:55.900
to just sit and be with myself
in a mode where I'm not judging

00:51:55.900 --> 00:51:59.790
or processing or
reacting to anything.

00:51:59.790 --> 00:52:04.480
And in terms of
what forms, I mean,

00:52:04.480 --> 00:52:06.230
really what I think
about it, I have

00:52:06.230 --> 00:52:09.660
been practicing this for much
longer than I even recognized.

00:52:09.660 --> 00:52:11.950
I started journaling
when I was nine years old

00:52:11.950 --> 00:52:17.580
and continued that regularly
up until a few years ago.

00:52:17.580 --> 00:52:19.065
And so that's a
form of meditation

00:52:19.065 --> 00:52:21.980
in a way as a
mindfulness practice.

00:52:21.980 --> 00:52:24.100
I practiced
meditation off and on.

00:52:24.100 --> 00:52:26.860
But honestly, it really
did not resonate with me

00:52:26.860 --> 00:52:30.070
until just a few years ago
when I combined it with yoga.

00:52:30.070 --> 00:52:32.400
So for a long time
for me personally,

00:52:32.400 --> 00:52:34.140
sitting alone and
just being with myself

00:52:34.140 --> 00:52:36.580
was really, really hard to do.

00:52:36.580 --> 00:52:40.150
And so I just directed
a lot of that energy

00:52:40.150 --> 00:52:41.850
into physical energy.

00:52:41.850 --> 00:52:45.410
So a lot of the
exercise that I do

00:52:45.410 --> 00:52:47.840
becomes meditative
in its own way,

00:52:47.840 --> 00:52:50.060
because I'm training
my mind to-- I

00:52:50.060 --> 00:52:53.100
engage in really highly
choreographed, high intensity

00:52:53.100 --> 00:52:56.300
cardio stuff.

00:52:56.300 --> 00:52:59.150
So that choreography
requires me to stay focused.

00:52:59.150 --> 00:53:03.020
Otherwise, if I go off thinking
about work or something,

00:53:03.020 --> 00:53:06.340
then I'll mess up and I won't
get the routine or whatever.

00:53:06.340 --> 00:53:10.010
So that's one way that
I use to train my mind.

00:53:10.010 --> 00:53:13.080
And then I also just
sit with myself.

00:53:13.080 --> 00:53:18.320
And even if it's in a moment
where I just don't have time

00:53:18.320 --> 00:53:24.040
to deliberately sit and om, just
taking a few mindful breaths

00:53:24.040 --> 00:53:27.836
is sometimes all it takes
to re-center myself.

00:53:27.836 --> 00:53:30.870
So I don't really think
of in terms of plateauing.

00:53:30.870 --> 00:53:32.715
It's a way of coming
back to center.

00:53:32.715 --> 00:53:33.590
Does that make sense?

00:53:40.338 --> 00:53:41.800
Anything else?

00:53:41.800 --> 00:53:47.250
OK, well thank you so much
